1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,680
[Episode 13]

2
00:00:01,680 --> 00:00:03,860
Chairman.

3
00:00:03,860 --> 00:00:08,200
- Why are you being so nice to me?
- Pardon?

4
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:11,770
Because you are so nice to me,

5
00:00:11,770 --> 00:00:16,430
my heart feels like it will explode.

6
00:00:19,450 --> 00:00:21,200
What did you say?

7
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:26,030
I think...

8
00:00:26,030 --> 00:00:28,110
I like you, Chairman.

9
00:00:28,110 --> 00:00:30,280
Whenever I see you,

10
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:33,470
my heart beats like crazy.

11
00:00:33,470 --> 00:00:36,820
Chairman, what if I get heart disease from this?

12
00:00:36,820 --> 00:00:42,540
Will you take responsibility if I get heart disease?

13
00:00:42,540 --> 00:00:45,440
Ms. Park.

14
00:00:45,440 --> 00:00:48,300
But don't worry.

15
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:53,440
I will not ask you to take responsibility for my heart.

16
00:00:53,440 --> 00:00:55,770
It's not your fault

17
00:00:55,770 --> 00:00:59,410
that my heart beats like this.

18
00:00:59,410 --> 00:01:02,970
I think you're pretty drunk.

19
00:01:02,970 --> 00:01:06,450
Let's go home now.

20
00:01:10,550 --> 00:01:12,680
Chairman.

21
00:01:12,690 --> 00:01:16,640
This is an absolute top secret.

22
00:01:21,300 --> 00:01:23,220
The truth is,

23
00:01:23,220 --> 00:01:25,570
you are...

24
00:01:25,570 --> 00:01:30,240
my first love.

25
00:01:30,270 --> 00:01:33,810
I think that's why

26
00:01:33,810 --> 00:01:36,490
my heart acts like this.

27
00:01:38,710 --> 00:01:41,680
What?

28
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:43,880
When I was young,

29
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:47,040
you gave me a ride on your bike.

30
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:49,770
At that time, I said go this way,

31
00:01:49,770 --> 00:01:52,160
go that way,

32
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:55,400
and gave you a hard time.

33
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:59,160
But you did everything I asked you to do.

34
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:02,530
The way you were like a fool

35
00:02:02,530 --> 00:02:06,170
was so cute to me.

36
00:02:06,170 --> 00:02:08,670
- Was I?
- Yes.

37
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:10,520
You seemed foolish

38
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:12,780
and cute and nice.

39
00:02:12,780 --> 00:02:18,330
On top of that, you're very handsome.

40
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:22,600
That's why I totally fell for you that day.

41
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:26,940
And I wished to see you again.

42
00:02:26,940 --> 00:02:29,950
But who knew

43
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:34,450
that I would not recognize you when I saw you again?

44
00:02:34,450 --> 00:02:37,300
How's that possible?

45
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:42,210
Ms. Park.

46
00:02:42,210 --> 00:02:47,230
I think we need to go inside now.

47
00:02:49,950 --> 00:02:59,180
Chairman, why did I not recognize you when you were the first love that I wanted to see again so badly?

48
00:02:59,180 --> 00:03:01,210
Try to guess it.

49
00:03:01,210 --> 00:03:04,570
Number one, because you were not wearing the military uniform.

50
00:03:04,570 --> 00:03:08,070
Two, because your hair style had changed.

51
00:03:08,070 --> 00:03:11,840
Three, because you became

52
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:16,680
so spectacularly handsome?

53
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:19,590
The correct answer is!

54
00:03:21,090 --> 00:03:22,790
Number three.

55
00:03:22,790 --> 00:03:28,940
It's because you became so handsome.

56
00:03:36,630 --> 00:03:42,590
Chairman, come catch me!

57
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:56,240
It's crazy, crazy, crazy!

58
00:03:56,250 --> 00:04:01,230
Hey, Park Dan Dan, what did you do?

59
00:04:01,230 --> 00:04:03,510
What do I do now!

60
00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:08,350
How do I face Chairman now?

61
00:04:08,350 --> 00:04:11,020
Should I run away right now?

62
00:04:11,020 --> 00:04:15,410
No, then what about Jenny, Se Chan, and Se Jong?

63
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:18,510
Should I say I'm sick and stay in bed?

64
00:04:18,510 --> 00:04:23,210
No, no. How long could I do that?

65
00:04:23,210 --> 00:04:24,790
Right.

66
00:04:24,790 --> 00:04:29,030
I don't remember anything from yesterday because I was too drunk.

67
00:04:29,030 --> 00:04:31,530
I have no memory of yesterday.

68
00:04:31,530 --> 00:04:34,530
I was blacked out. Blacked out!

69
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:39,120
I must have lost my mind!

70
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:42,420
What should I do?

71
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:46,830
