Kyung Sook, you wench!

781
00:52:41,630 --> 00:52:43,870
Please go inside.

782
00:52:46,500 --> 00:52:49,510
Ms. Park, is it--

783
00:52:49,510 --> 00:52:54,590
That's right! Madam did something unspeakable to Ms. Park again.

784
00:52:54,590 --> 00:52:57,300
What is this? Let's talk later.

785
00:52:57,300 --> 00:53:01,730
Ms. Park is not in a good state. Let's go upstairs.

786
00:53:01,730 --> 00:53:04,150
Are you okay?

787
00:53:13,520 --> 00:53:16,930
I thought we only had to get rid of Mrs. Yeoju, but what's this?

788
00:53:16,930 --> 00:53:20,240
Who would have thought the Chairman would be home early? And that woman, Anna too!

789
00:53:20,240 --> 00:53:22,150
What am I going to do now?

790
00:53:22,150 --> 00:53:24,500
Mom, I think it'd be best for you to go home.

791
00:53:24,500 --> 00:53:25,930
Right, I will.

792
00:53:25,930 --> 00:53:28,960
- Let me go with you.
- No, Madam!

793
00:53:28,960 --> 00:53:32,800
You have to pretend to be sick and sleep.

794
00:53:32,800 --> 00:53:36,740
Since things have come to this, I'll go and confront it with the Chairman right now.

795
00:53:36,740 --> 00:53:39,270
- Mom, I told you to go.
- Okay.

796
00:53:39,270 --> 00:53:42,850
Dae Ran, you got this, okay?

797
00:53:43,940 --> 00:53:45,710
Madam, please lie down.

798
00:53:45,710 --> 00:53:49,940
What do you mean by confronting it with the Chairman?

799
00:53:49,940 --> 00:53:54,110
Whenever Madam sees Ms. Park, her symptoms get worse.

800
00:53:54,110 --> 00:53:58,170
Then Ms. Park should quit. Don't you think so?

801
00:53:58,170 --> 00:54:00,790
Yes. Yes.

802
00:54:00,790 --> 00:54:03,100
Of course.

803
00:54:04,100 --> 00:54:07,060
Your clothes and everything is a mess right now.

804
00:54:07,060 --> 00:54:08,830
What kind of craziness is this?

805
00:54:08,830 --> 00:54:11,400
Clothes can be washed. It's okay.

806
00:54:11,400 --> 00:54:14,770
What do you mean by it's okay! You got attacked vulnerably.

807
00:54:14,770 --> 00:54:17,290
How can you say it's okay?

808
00:54:17,290 --> 00:54:20,580
It's because Madam is sick.

809
00:54:22,640 --> 00:54:25,860
Ms. Park.

810
00:54:25,860 --> 00:54:31,250
Are you working here even enduring all these things because you have nowhere else to go?

811
00:54:31,250 --> 00:54:33,090
I told you.

812
00:54:33,090 --> 00:54:36,770
You can work with me, so--

813
00:54:36,770 --> 00:54:40,030
That's not the only reason.

814
00:54:40,030 --> 00:54:42,330
I have a place to go now.

815
00:54:42,330 --> 00:54:48,410
I can go home. And I have saved some money too.

816
00:54:48,410 --> 00:54:52,320
It's just because...

817
00:54:52,320 --> 00:54:56,990
I like working here and it gives me joy.

818
00:54:56,990 --> 00:55:03,530
It makes me happy and grateful that someone needs me.

819
00:55:03,550 --> 00:55:08,720
That's why I want to stay here.

820
00:55:08,720 --> 00:55:15,370
My sweet Dan Dan, if staying here makes her happy, then she should stay.

821
00:55:15,370 --> 00:55:19,180
Next to me like this.

822
00:55:19,180 --> 00:55:23,640
I know that Madam is not acting like that on purpose,

823
00:55:23,640 --> 00:55:29,300
and it's all because of her illness, but it still upsets me.

824
00:55:29,300 --> 00:55:34,950
And it makes me worry that she might get worse because of me.

825
00:55:34,950 --> 00:55:37,550
So should I leave here?

826
00:55:37,550 --> 00:55:41,140
I don't know what to do.

827
00:55:49,190 --> 00:55:52,510
Ms. Park, don't worry.

828
00:55:52,510 --> 00:55:55,360
We will find the right solutions.

829
00:55:55,360 --> 00:56:01,000
And now that Chairman knows everything, he won't let this happen again.

830
00:56:01,000 --> 00:56:04,110
So let's get changed, Ms. Park.

831
00:56:04,110 --> 00:56:07,230
And rest comfortably, okay?

832
00:56:07,230 --> 00:56:10,420
Yes. Thank you.

833
00:56:10,420 --> 00:56:12,920
It will be okay.

834
00:56:28,250 --> 00:56:32,280
Madam's behavioral symptoms are not for early stages.

835
00:56:32,280 --> 00:56:35,320
She can't act like this if she's at an early stage.

836
00:56:38,860 --> 00:56:45,630
What do you mean Ms. Park should resign, Chief Jo?

837
00:56:45,630 --> 00:56:51,560
Madam seems to act quite normal when Ms. Park is not around,

838
00:56:51,560 --> 00:56:56,200
but whenever she sees her, whether because of hallucinations or unhappy memories,

839
00:56:56,200 --> 00:56:59,130
her condition gets worse.

840
00:56:59,130 --> 00:57:02,450
Even still, Ms. Park is working hard and doing well.

841
00:57:02,450 --> 00:57:08,020
How about if we send her on a long vacation, so she doesn't appear in front of Madam?

842
00:57:08,020 --> 00:57:11,610
Until Madam gets settled, perhaps.

843
00:57:14,100 --> 00:57:21,960
I think it'd be better for Madam to go to a nursing home for a while.

844
00:57:21,960 --> 00:57:26,050
A nursing home? That doesn't make any sense.

845
00:57:26,050 --> 00:57:27,210
She's still at an early stage.

846
00:57:27,210 --> 00:57:31,630
From what I see, she's not at the early stage but a severe stage.

847
00:57:31,630 --> 00:57:33,940
You saw how Ms. Park was covered in tomato juice.

848
00:57:33,940 --> 00:57:36,610
Madam did that, didn't she?

849
00:57:38,270 --> 00:57:40,530
That is...

850
00:57:40,530 --> 00:57:43,980
And she was telling her to get out and pushing her to the floor.

851
00:57:43,980 --> 00:57:46,880
A good thing the children weren't there. What if they saw it?

852
00:57:46,880 --> 00:57:50,300
They would have been in a big shock.

853
00:57:50,300 --> 00:57:55,430
Did she really do that to Ms. Park?

854
00:57:55,430 --> 00:57:58,110
If she's at the early stage of dementia, that couldn't happen.

855
00:57:58,110 --> 00:58:01,390
There must have been a mistake in diagnosis.

856
00:58:01,390 --> 00:58:05,510
Chief Jo, did she get a proper dementia examination?

857
00:58:05,510 --> 00:58:09,570
I know you didn't go to Dr. Kim. Where did you go for the test?

858
00:58:09,570 --> 00:58:15,490
Madam didn't want to go there because she was too embarrassed.

859
00:58:15,490 --> 00:58:20,570
So we went to a different, small hospital.

860
00:58:22,440 --> 00:58:29,740
Young Gook. What if she gets this violent toward the children? I get the chill just imagining it.

861
00:58:29,740 --> 00:58:33,870
Putting everything aside, it's in the best interest of Madam for her

862
00:58:33,870 --> 00:58:36,010
to get help from specialists.

863
00:58:36,010 --> 00:58:40,320
I heard there are many good nursing homes nowadays.

864
00:58:40,320 --> 00:58:42,460
Yes, I agree.

865
00:58:42,460 --> 00:58:45,120
I will go talk to her.

866
00:58:52,100 --> 00:58:55,710
How long do I have to lie here like this?

867
00:59:03,260 --> 00:59:05,880
If you feel okay, can you sit up?

868
00:59:05,880 --> 00:59:08,140
Ah, yes.

869
00:59:08,140 --> 00:59:10,080
Oh, my head.

870
00:59:10,080 --> 00:59:13,940
Why does my head hurt so much?

871
00:59:13,940 --> 00:59:17,320
Do you recognize me?

872
00:59:17,320 --> 00:59:21,380
Chairman Lee! I'm at the early stage of dementia.

873
00:59:21,380 --> 00:59:23,540
I am okay.

874
00:59:23,540 --> 00:59:27,470
Then do you remember what you did to Ms. Park?

875
00:59:27,470 --> 00:59:31,490
Ms. Park? What did I do to her?

876
00:59:31,490 --> 00:59:34,370
You don't remember?

877
00:59:34,370 --> 00:59:37,670
I guess I did something to her again.

878
00:59:37,670 --> 00:59:40,090
Yang Kyung Sook and such.

879
00:59:40,090 --> 00:59:41,840
Yes.

880
00:59:41,840 --> 00:59:46,190
Oh, what am I going to do?

881
00:59:46,190 --> 00:59:50,860
So please go to Dr. Kim and get a thorough examination tomorrow.

882
00:59:50,860 --> 00:59:56,080
And why don't you get treatment in a good nursing home for a while?

883
00:59:57,870 --> 00:59:59,690
A nursing home?

884
00:59:59,690 --> 01:00:01,810
What nursing home?

885
01:00:01,810 --> 01:00:05,160
I think you are in serious condition.

886
01:00:05,160 --> 01:00:08,910
We've never had anyone named Yang Kyung Sook work in our house.

887
01:00:08,910 --> 01:00:12,950
Even so, you treat Ms. Park in a hostile manner.

888
01:00:12,950 --> 01:00:17,920
I don't want my children to see such violent behavior.

889
01:00:19,600 --> 01:00:23,520
The truth is, Chairman Lee...

890
01:00:23,520 --> 01:00:26,770
For our children, please go to the nursing home.

891
01:00:26,770 --> 01:00:29,850
I will make sure you get the best treatment possible.

892
01:00:29,850 --> 01:00:34,310
No, that's not it! What treatment do I need in a nursing home?

893
01:00:34,310 --> 01:00:38,440
I'm not going to a nursing home. I'm not going there!

894
01:00:38,440 --> 01:00:41,450
Please do so. I won't give you a hard time.

895
01:00:41,450 --> 01:00:43,800
Chairman Lee!

896
01:00:43,800 --> 01:00:49,590
Young Gook. I don't have dementia.

897
01:00:49,590 --> 01:00:51,890
It was fake dementia.

898
01:00:51,890 --> 01:00:55,280
I don't have dementia.

899
01:00:55,280 --> 01:00:56,360
What?

900
01:00:56,360 --> 01:00:59,360
I never went to the hospital.

901
01:00:59,360 --> 01:01:02,020
Nor did I get diagnosed with dementia.

902
01:01:02,020 --> 01:01:08,580
I was just acting a show. I just acted like I was crazy!

903
01:01:08,590 --> 01:01:13,350
What are you saying right now?

904
01:01:13,350 --> 01:01:15,760
- What kind of nonsense!
- No, no.

905
01:01:15,760 --> 01:01:18,800
Young Gook, Young Gook.

906
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:22,150
Because you seem to have feelings for Ms. Park.

907
01:01:22,150 --> 01:01:24,230
You shouldn't do that!

908
01:01:24,230 --> 01:01:25,980
What kind of household are we?

909
01:01:25,980 --> 01:01:28,870
What kind of company our FT Group is?

910
01:01:28,870 --> 01:01:33,540
If a strange rumor spreads about you and Ms. Park, it's a big problem!

911
01:01:33,540 --> 01:01:34,930
That's why I did it.

912
01:01:34,930 --> 01:01:40,130
I wanted to kick Ms. Park out quietly.

913
01:01:40,130 --> 01:01:42,340
For that reason,

914
01:01:42,340 --> 01:01:44,640
that's why you pretended to have dementia?

915
01:01:44,640 --> 01:01:47,260
Chairman Lee, I'd lost my mind.

916
01:01:47,260 --> 01:01:49,840
At that time, I'd lost my mind--

917
01:01:49,840 --> 01:01:52,540
Get out of my house now!

918
01:01:52,540 --> 01:01:55,260
Chairman Lee, Chairman Lee.

919
01:01:55,260 --> 01:02:00,390
You lied in front of my children and accused an innocent person of stealing!

920
01:02:00,390 --> 01:02:06,640
And then you pretended to have dementia. How can you humanly do that?

921
01:02:06,640 --> 01:02:09,850
Chairman Lee, Chairman Lee. I did wrong.

922
01:02:09,850 --> 01:02:14,480
I'm sorry, Chairman Lee. I was out of my mind!

923
01:02:14,480 --> 01:02:17,160
I can't live with you anymore, no matter what you say.

924
01:02:17,160 --> 01:02:20,710
So please leave. Get out right now!

925
01:02:20,710 --> 01:02:23,490
Okay, I get it.

926
01:02:23,490 --> 01:02:28,240
I will go.

927
01:02:29,750 --> 01:02:33,990
But not until my daughter Se Ryun gets married.

928
01:02:33,990 --> 01:02:36,760
Can I please stay until then?

929
01:02:36,760 --> 01:02:42,820
I know you hate me, but Se Ryun is your only sister.

930
01:02:42,820 --> 01:02:46,280
We can't let Se Ryun pay for my mistake.

931
01:02:46,280 --> 01:02:52,710
Chairman Lee, I'm begging you like this!

932
01:02:52,710 --> 01:02:56,170
I'm begging you, Chairman Lee.

933
01:02:56,170 --> 01:03:01,180
I'm sorry, Chairman Lee.

934
01:03:01,180 --> 01:03:03,740
Chairman Lee.

935
01:03:10,040 --> 01:03:12,120
Chief Jo!

936
01:03:12,120 --> 01:03:15,260
Yes, Chairman.

937
01:03:15,260 --> 01:03:18,450
Come to my study, now.

938
01:03:20,880 --> 01:03:26,880
Chief Jo. That she didn't go to the hospital nor get examined,

939
01:03:26,880 --> 01:03:30,050
is that all true?

940
01:03:30,050 --> 01:03:31,650
Yes.

941
01:03:31,650 --> 01:03:36,900
Are you saying you reported lies to me?

942
01:03:36,900 --> 01:03:39,130
I'm sorry, Chairman.

943
01:03:39,130 --> 01:03:43,870
I had no choice since Madam asked me to do so.

944
01:03:43,870 --> 01:03:46,410
Are you giving me that as an excuse?

945
01:03:46,410 --> 01:03:48,130
I'm sorry.

946
01:03:48,130 --> 01:03:52,460
I am seriously disappointed with you, Chief Jo.

947
01:03:52,460 --> 01:03:56,300
Chairman, but this is my first time.

948
01:03:56,300 --> 01:04:01,240
I've never lied to you before. I swear!

949
01:04:01,240 --> 01:04:04,500
That's enough. Please leave.

950
01:04:17,880 --> 01:04:22,430
Why were you shouting at Chief Jo?

951
01:04:24,140 --> 01:04:27,500
It's nothing.

952
01:04:27,500 --> 01:04:29,670
What did Madam say?

953
01:04:29,670 --> 01:04:34,340
Did you talk to her about the nursing home?

954
01:04:34,340 --> 01:04:37,600
She will not do anything like that from now on.

955
01:04:37,600 --> 01:04:39,530
Just leave it at that , Noona.

956
01:04:39,530 --> 01:04:44,290
What are you saying? If you leave it, she will do that again to Ms. Park.

957
01:04:44,290 --> 01:04:47,680
No, she won't do anything like that again.

958
01:04:47,680 --> 01:04:49,400
Let's leave it at that.

959
01:04:49,400 --> 01:04:53,250
I will take care of this myself.

960
01:04:55,430 --> 01:05:00,470
Okay, that's good then.

961
01:05:00,470 --> 01:05:04,250
Is Ms. Park okay?

962
01:05:04,250 --> 01:05:07,980
She says she's okay, but I think it was very hard on her.

963
01:05:07,980 --> 01:05:11,400
She even thought about quitting here.

964
01:05:11,400 --> 01:05:14,790
Is that really true?

965
01:05:14,790 --> 01:05:18,120
Of course. Why wouldn't she think about it when that kind of thing happened to her?

966
01:05:18,120 --> 01:05:21,480
Get some rest. I'm going to my room.

967
01:05:39,820 --> 01:05:44,690
Ms. Park, please come out to the front of the house for a minute.

968
01:05:59,980 --> 01:06:03,660
Ms. Park, please get in.

969
01:06:03,660 --> 01:06:04,710
Pardon?

970
01:06:04,710 --> 01:06:07,220
Please get in first.

971
01:06:15,690 --> 01:06:18,230
And put your seatbelt on.

972
01:06:18,230 --> 01:06:20,380
Chairman, where are we going?

973
01:06:20,380 --> 01:06:22,650
Hurry up and put on the seatbelt.

974
01:06:27,210 --> 01:06:29,600
Let's go now.

975
01:06:39,790 --> 01:06:41,930
Please drink.

976
01:06:41,930 --> 01:06:44,900
Why don't you have a sip?

977
01:06:47,810 --> 01:06:50,780
How is it? Does it make you feel better?

978
01:06:50,780 --> 01:06:55,880
You told me once that your mood gets better when you drink this.

979
01:06:55,900 --> 01:07:01,230
Did you remember all that?

980
01:07:01,230 --> 01:07:03,270
I have a very good memory.

981
01:07:03,270 --> 01:07:06,440
Ms. Park, what should we do now?

982
01:07:06,440 --> 01:07:08,890
Yes, you like playing the whack-a-mole.

983
01:07:08,890 --> 01:07:12,090
Let's go catch some moles.

984
01:07:12,090 --> 01:07:15,170
What are you doing? Let's go.

985
01:07:36,150 --> 01:07:39,280
Come on, whack them.

986
01:07:50,380 --> 01:07:53,950
How was I? I even caught your moles too.

987
01:07:53,950 --> 01:07:57,950
I did better than the last time. Didn't I improve a lot?

988
01:07:59,640 --> 01:08:04,810
Are you still upset, Ms. Park?

989
01:08:04,810 --> 01:08:10,000
I guess it'd be hard to feel totally better with this.

990
01:08:10,000 --> 01:08:13,460
Since we couldn't do it with whack-a-mole, how about a bike ride?

991
01:08:13,460 --> 01:08:16,490
It's breezy out, perfect for bike riding.

992
01:08:16,490 --> 01:08:20,320
Should we ride about thirty rounds today?

993
01:08:22,690 --> 01:08:26,240
Chairman.

994
01:08:26,240 --> 01:08:29,730
Why do you act like this to me?

995
01:08:29,730 --> 01:08:39,430
Do you also have feelings for me?

996
01:08:39,430 --> 01:08:43,600
That's it, isn't it?

997
01:08:43,600 --> 01:08:51,270
♫ Why do you run away, love. Like a shy child ♫

998
01:08:51,270 --> 01:08:58,040
♫ In case I lose it. I hold it tight ♫

999
01:08:58,040 --> 01:09:05,050
♫ But love always runs away, chased by longing ♫

1000
01:09:05,050 --> 01:09:11,850
♫ It would be nice to take a break ♫

1001
01:09:11,850 --> 01:09:19,850
♫ I have to abandon the longing and the grieves ♫

1002
01:09:19,850 --> 01:09:25,930
♫ What am I looking for on this road wandering ♫

1003
01:09:25,930 --> 01:09:32,290
♫  Why am I here for what  ♫

1004
01:09:32,290 --> 01:09:35,180
[Young Lady and Gentleman]

1005
01:09:35,180 --> 01:09:36,730
It's my friend's story.

1006
01:09:36,730 --> 01:09:40,800
- A woman with quite a bit of age gap likes him.
- Good luck!

1007
01:09:40,800 --> 01:09:41,880
It's not me, I told you.

1008
01:09:41,880 --> 01:09:43,830
Please take this necklace.

1009
01:09:43,830 --> 01:09:45,140
Why are you giving this to me?

1010
01:09:45,140 --> 01:09:46,860
It's because I'm so sorry.

1011
01:09:46,860 --> 01:09:51,220
Does it make sense I can't get rid of that country bumpkin even with Madam's help?

1012
01:09:51,220 --> 01:09:54,310
There is no one without a flaw. You will find something if you shake them.

1013
01:09:54,310 --> 01:09:56,790
There will be a way to kick her out.

1014
01:09:56,790 --> 01:10:00,430
We've set the wedding date. It's the second Saturday next month.

1015
01:10:00,430 --> 01:10:01,290
That's good.

1016
01:10:01,290 --> 01:10:04,510
Are you really going to marry that guy? It doesn't matter for me who you marry.

1017
01:10:04,510 --> 01:10:06,010
But he's not okay!

1018
01:10:06,010 --> 01:10:07,390
Why do you care?

1019
01:10:07,390 --> 01:10:09,080
What does it matter to you!

1020
01:10:09,080 --> 01:10:13,320
If you like me too, please hang the handkerchief on this tree by tomorrow.

1021
01:10:13,320 --> 01:10:14,510
What should I do?

1022
01:10:14,510 --> 01:10:16,500
I am back.

1023
01:10:16,500 --> 01:10:18,290
What are you? Who are you?

1024
01:10:18,290 --> 01:10:20,170
Are you really Driver Park's daughter?
